<typeStatus id="AC2AC983FFECFFEFFB3E23DFDED0FD7A" box="[1196,1246,724,750]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">type</typeStatus>
series that have the front white tomentose, without golden scales. Some of the males have dark hair on the second antennal segment.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3B8B24AAFFECFFEFFEAA2240DBC2FC22" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="732E7721FFECFFEFFEAA2240DBC2FC22" blockId="59.[264,1325,284,1150]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis id="41E5AB33FFECFFEFFEAA2240DBB2FCF1" bold="true" box="[312,444,843,869]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Discussion</emphasis>
. This species has been collected with 
<taxonomicName id="B4910CA2FFECFFEFFC042247DE10FCF1" box="[918,1054,844,869]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Geron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripes">
<emphasis id="41E5AB33FFECFFEFFC042247DE10FCF1" box="[918,1054,844,869]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">G. nigripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The two species are, however, easily separated by the configuration of both the male (cf. 
<figureCitation id="EBAA6BA4FFECFFEFFBA7227FDE9BFC1A" box="[1077,1173,884,910]" captionStart="FIGURES 42 – 45" captionStartId="37.[264,382,1744,1768]" captionTargetBox="[327,1255,636,1719]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[316,1273,632,1721]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURES 42 – 45. Geron male genitalia. 42, G. johnsoni Painter; a, lateral view; b, tip of gonocoxa, ventral view. 43, G. monticola Hall &amp; Evenhuis, sp. nov.; a, lateral view; b, gonocoxa, dorsal view. 44, G. nevadensis Hall &amp; Evenhuis, sp. nov.; a, lateral view; b, tip of gonocoxa, dorsal view. 45, G. nigripes Painter; a, lateral view; b, gonocoxa, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/156853/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
Figs. 
<number id="C5596506FFECFFEFFBEA227FDE9BFC1A" box="[1144,1173,884,910]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" value="45.0">45</number>
</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="EBAA6BA4FFECFFEFFB43227FDEFEFC1A" box="[1233,1264,884,910]" captionStart="FIGURES 54 – 57" captionStartId="58.[264,382,1407,1431]" captionTargetBox="[322,1258,473,1378]" captionTargetId="figure@58.[319,1262,466,1386]" captionTargetPageId="58" captionText="FIGURES 54 – 57. Geron male genitalia. 53, G. stenos Hall &amp; Evenhuis, sp. nov.; a, lateral view; b, gonocoxa, ventral view. 55, G. subauratus Loew; a, lateral view; b, gonocoxa, ventral view. 56, G. vitripennis Loew; a, lateral view; b, tip of gonocoxa, ventral view. 57, G. weemsi Hall &amp; Evenhuis, sp. nov.; a, lateral view; b, gonocoxa, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/156856/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<number id="C5596506FFECFFEFFB43227FDEFEFC1A" box="[1233,1264,884,910]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" value="54.0">54</number>
</figureCitation>
) and female genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3B8B24AAFFECFFEFFEAA22C8DB27FB92" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="732E7721FFECFFEFFEAA22C8DB27FB92" blockId="59.[264,1325,284,1150]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis id="41E5AB33FFECFFEFFEAA22C8DB9AFC49" bold="true" box="[312,404,963,989]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Biology</emphasis>
. Immature stages unknown. Adults have been taken at flowers of 
<taxonomicName id="B4910CA2FFECFFEFFB3522CFDF25FC49" box="[1191,1323,964,989]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Eriogonum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polygonales" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="41E5AB33FFECFFEFFB3522CFDF25FC49" box="[1191,1323,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Eriogonum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
