<subSubSection id="3B8B24AAFFECFFEFFEAA2530DE6BFBEA" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="732E7721FFECFFEFFEAA2530DE6BFBEA" blockId="59.[264,1325,284,1150]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis id="41E5AB33FFECFFEFFEAA2530DBB3FBC1" bold="true" box="[312,445,1083,1109]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific epithet derives from the Greek “ ” = narrow appearance; referring to the relatively narrow 
<emphasis id="41E5AB33FFECFFEFFD47256FD92DFBE9" box="[725,803,1124,1149]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">gestalt</emphasis>
of the body of this species.
</paragraph>
